						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone near the Parvatadēva temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>Mārassaḻba—undated.</p>						

						<p>This fragmentary inscription in characters of about the <hi rend="bold">8th century A.D.,</hi> refers itself to the reign of a king named <hi rend="bold">Mārassaḻba.</hi></p>						

						<p>It mentions one <hi rend="bold">Daḍigarasa</hi> as governing <hi rend="bold">nāḍu</hi> and also a certain Śubhachandrapaṇḍita. Mention is also made of a <hi rend="italic">ṁēṇṭi</hi> of <hi rend="italic">gōsāsa</hi> of Indamma.</p>						

						<p>The inscription is published in <hi rend="italic">Ep. Ind.,</hi> Vol. VI, p. 257.</p>						

						</summary>
